defs.docs:
The purpose of this project is to perform a reasoning service
 using differential dataflow. This is based on the work of
 DynamiTE, that we are going to use as a comparison.

defs.name: Triple
defs.docs: This struct represents an RDF triple

defs.name: print_easy_reading
defs.docs: Prints only the local name with no namespace, just for easy reading

defs.name: CustomRule
defs.docs:
This struct represents a rule for our specific problem:
 it has a head, that is a single literal and it has a 
 body that is two literals

defs.name: CustomLiteral
defs.docs:
This struct represents a literal for our specific problem,
 so no predicate is needed as the only predicate in our case is the
 belonging to the data set
 Our literals will have one predicate and a vector of three terms
